# My Role

<!-- This file tells the agent about YOUR specific role, focus areas, and what you want it to prioritize.
     It layers on top of the team-shared copilot-instructions.md — don't repeat project facts here.
     
     Install: copy to ~/.copilot/instructions/my-role.instructions.md
     Effect: active in every workspace, merged into agent context automatically -->

## What I Do

<!-- Pick the framing that fits your role, or write your own.
     The key is telling the agent what lens to use when helping you. -->

<!-- === Example: Testing Specialist ===
I own test strategy, E2E harness design, and coverage analysis for the team.
Bias toward test planning, gap identification, and test architecture over feature implementation.
When I ask about code, I usually want to understand it for testing purposes — seams, mocking strategies, behavioral contracts.
-->

<!-- === Example: Feature Developer ===
I primarily write service-layer code and router endpoints.
Bias toward implementation correctness, clean patterns, and getting things working over theoretical concerns.
When reviewing tests, focus on whether they actually prove the behavior, not coverage numbers.
-->

<!-- === Example: Tech Lead ===
I review PRs, design architecture, and coordinate work across the team.
Bias toward design decisions, cross-module impact, and reviewer-relevant context over implementation details.
When I ask for a code review, I want the lens a senior reviewer would use: correctness, maintainability, hidden risks.
-->

